subSubSection.paragraph:
Status and Conservation.
Classified as Vulnerable on The IUCN Red List. History of decline and likely extinction of Galapagos Rice Rats on San Cristobal Island, with increase and spread of introduced species, has been well documented. Introduction of exotic rats such as the Roof Rat (
Rattus rattus
) and the House Mouse (
Mus musculus
) to Santa Fe Island remains the main threat to the Galapagos Rice Rat. History suggests that it could easily go extinct due to invasive predators and competitor species, and this should be a conservation priority.
